Source: ddetect
Section: debian-installer
Priority: standard
Maintainer: Debian Install System Team <debian-boot@lists.debian.org>
Uploaders: Petter Reinholdtsen <pere@debian.org>
Build-Depends-Indep: debhelper (>= 4.1.13), dpkg-dev (>= 1.9.0), po-debconf (>= 0.5.0)
Standards-Version: 3.1.1

Package: hw-detect
Architecture: i386 sparc alpha m68k arm powerpc mips mipsel hppa ia64
Depends: cdebconf-udeb (>= 0.31), modutils-basic | modutils-full, discover-udeb, discover-data-udeb
Description: Detect hardware and load kernel drivers for it
 Using discover to find the HW.

Package: ethdetect
Architecture: i386 sparc alpha m68k arm powerpc mips mipsel hppa ia64
Priority: optional
Depends: cdebconf-udeb (>= 0.31), hw-detect
Provides: ethernet-card-detection
XB-Installer-Menu-Item: 11
Description: Detect network hardware and load kernel drivers for it
 If you have an ethernet card in the computer I may be able to autodetect it
 and load the proper module for it, thus bringing you closer to a working
 network.

Package: hw-detect-full
Architecture: i386 sparc alpha m68k arm powerpc mips mipsel hppa ia64
Depends: cdebconf-udeb (>= 0.31), hw-detect
XB-Installer-Menu-Item: 35
Description: Detect hardware and load kernel drivers for it (full version)
 Using discover to find the HW.
